\par\plain {\f0\fs22 Fusion}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 People always get hung up on terminology differences between the Urantia book and Course in Miracles. Some say how can I accept a course that says sin is an illusion or sin does not exist. My response is how can you accept the Urantia book when it says sin is a cosmic unreality, and that sin is not a spirit reality. We can even find quotes in the Urantia book from Jesus who says \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93My brother, God is love; therefore he must be good, and his goodness is so great and real that it cannot contain the small and UNREAL THINGS OF EVIL.\u8221\'94 Was that a mistake in the Urantia book? Did Jesus really say that? He didn\u8217\'92t mean it literally did he?  According to the UB sin is unreal. Where else besides the Urantia book and Course in Miracles will you hear that kind of language? And where else will you hear about the possibility of passing to a higher reality without dying? What is the purpose of the Course? Is it to live in the world and be of the world? Or is the goal to transcend time and see at least to the morontia semi spirit level? }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 And the text surely doesn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t recommend you dismiss this reality and say oh so what and I don\u8217\'92t need to care or do anything.  The text says it wants active participants. It even gave us a slogan, listen, learn and do. \u8220\'93 Listen to my voice, learn to undo error, and do something to correct it. The first two are not enough. The real members of my party are active workers.\u8221\'94 Do something to correct it. You can\u8217\'92t read one lesson and say oh that is so wrong. It is a Course and the text is a vital part of it. If you just want to live in this world and identify every evil and every sin and attack it in the name of saving humanity then maybe the Course is not for you. Because the Course is clearly a guide to transcend time and get in touch with our higher mind, morontia mind. And the Urantia book clearly says adjuster fusion is a lofty goal. What is fusion but doing God\u8217\'92s will perfectly. After all this is exactly what Jesus did. \u8220\'93What is the face of Christ but his who went a moment into timelessness and brought a clear reflection of the unity he felt an instant back to bless the world?\u8221\'94.  So it is unfair to classify the course as some kind of irresponsible advocate for not caring. How can that be when it constantly emphasizes our sonship with each other? It constantly encourages us to forgive each other and turn to the Holy Spirit for guidance in what to do next. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
