\par\plain {\f0\fs22 Personality survival}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 Regarding personality extinction this is what the Urantia book says about that. First, this: 109:3.2 \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Nothing of survival value is ever lost in all the wide universe.\u8221\'94 From an eternal perspective there is no danger of losing anything that matters. Hence no fear. The personality will survive, the adjuster will survive, even the experiences of the lost identity of the human will survive in the adjuster. The part that does not survive is the IDENTITY of the human being. That is a purely temporal creation. No danger ever exists in eternity. The idea that God or Jesus would create some kind of reality (temporal) and then subject something that was changeless and eternal (personality) to a potential eternal death is as heartless as the atonement doctrine of Christianity (that God required his perfect son\u8217\'92s life on the cross as ransom for a creation he no longer loves). }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 These words in the Urantia book are plain and simple. It says personality will attain deity destiny. It never changes, it will not die. What dies is the human identity in time, a purely temporal creation. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 112:5.2 Having appeared in response to the Father's will, PERSONALITY WILL ATTAIN DEITY DESTINY, but man must choose whether or not he will be present at the attainment of such destiny. IN DEFAULT OF SUCH CHOICE, PERSONALITY ATTAINS EXPERIENTIAL DEITY DIRECTLY, becoming a part of the Supreme Being. The cycle is foreordained, but man's participation therein is optional, personal, and experiential.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 When it says \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93mans participation\u8221\'94 it is referring to identity in time, not personality in eternity. Eternity is an impossible concept for us to comprehend. We can only logically think about the idea that something is changeless and has always existed. This is how the Urantia book describes personality. It is unchanging in the face of change. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 112:5.20 Human life is an endless change of the factors of life unified by the stability of the unchanging personality.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 It is the one CHANGELESS REALITY in an otherwise ever-changing creature experience. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 0:5.11Personality. The personality of mortal man is neither body, mind, nor spirit; neither is it the soul. PERSONALITY IS THE ONE CHANGELESS REALITY in an otherwise ever-changing creature experience}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 In the next quote it says never again does it (identity) appear as a personality. It\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s identity becomes a though it had never been. Here we are talking about identity not personality. Personality becomes a part of the supreme being. It is important to differentiate between personality and identity. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 2:3.4 When the continued embrace of sin by the associated mind culminates in complete self-identification with iniquity, then upon the cessation of life, upon cosmic dissolution, such an isolated PERSONALITY is absorbed into the oversoul of creation, BECOMING A PART OF THE EVOLVING EXPERIENCE OF THE SUPREME BEING. Never again does it appear as a personality; its IDENTITY becomes as though it had never been.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\cf1
