\par\pard\plain \sa160\sl259\slmult1\ltrch\loch \f0\fs22\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22 I believe the Course in Miracles is a course in Adjuster fusion. It is given through auto revelation as opposed to epical revelation as the UB was. Studying the Course in Miracles has helped me to see the eternal perspective in the Urantia book more clearly. The Urantia book points out the paradox of trying to reconcile the temporal with the eternal. The two are opposing thought systems. In order to transcend this reality we need to flip our point of view from the temporal to the eternal. Both the Urantia book and Course in Miracles point out the conflict that must be traversed when transitioning from the temporal to the eternal. It will be an abstract journey with religious experiences that cannot be put into words. The Course in Miracles is very abstract yet on closer examination you will find identical concepts described with slightly different terminology. That is what I find most amazing. For instance, both the Urantia book and Course in Miracles say a miracle shortens time. They both say the goal of time is to unite the Sonship (God the Supreme). Both acknowledge Lucifer\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s rebellion and Adamic default in slightly different ways. Both say there are levels of learning that must be traversed (Circle attainment). The eternal viewpoint really pops out of the Urantia book when you study the Course in Miracles as a course in Adjuster fusion. The confusion comes in when you talk to a Course in Miracles student who has never studied the Urantia book and has no idea what fusion is. I suggest looking at the Course as meant to compliment the Urantia book. I see it as Jesus relating what he learned during his life in the flesh. He is teaching us the path he made to the final father as he learned it. The Course in Miracles has also given me an deeper understanding of how the Holy Spirit works. The Course in Miracles teaches that forgiveness is critical to accessing the higher mind functions of the superconscious. Yes the Course is very abstract. But consider how much the apostles struggled to understand what Jesus was teaching them in their time. Wouldn\u8217\'92t it make sense that Jesus would share his path to the final father with us and that we might struggle just as the apostles have to understand his teachings?\line \line 2 - (101:6.17) Through the appropriation of the faith of Jesus, mortal man can foretaste in time the realities of eternity. Jesus made the discovery, in human experience, of the Final Father, and his brothers in the flesh of mortal life can follow him along this same experience of Father discovery. They can even attain, as they are, the same satisfaction in this experience with the Father as did Jesus as he was. New potentials were actualized in the universe of Nebadon consequent upon the terminal bestowal of Michael, and one of these was the new illumination of the path of eternity that leads to the Father of all, and which can be traversed even by the mortals of material flesh and blood in the initial life on the planets of space. Jesus was and is the new and living way whereby man can come into the divine inheritance which the Father has decreed shall be his for but the asking. In Jesus there is abundantly demonstrated both the beginnings and endings of the faith experience of humanity, even of divine humanity.}
