\par\plain {\f2\fs24 1:5.12 \~In the contemplation of Deity, the concept of personality must be divested of the idea of corporeality. A MATERIAL BODY IS NOT INDISPENSABLE TO PERSONALITY IN EITHER MAN OR GOD. The corporeality error is shown in both extremes of human philosophy. In materialism, since man loses his body at death, he ceases to exist as a personality; in pantheism, since God has no body, he is not, therefore, a person. THE SUPERHUMAN TYPE OF PROGRESSING PERSONALITY FUNCTIONS IN A UNION OF MIND AND SPIRIT.}
